President Obama has appointed Elizabeth Warren as Assistant to the President and Special Advisor to the Secretary of the Treasury on the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau. Warren will be responsible for setting up the Bureau and ensuring its effectiveness. The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau will focus on cracking down on abusive practices by mortgage lenders, enforcing fair credit card laws, and protecting consumers from overdraft fees. Warren is a renowned law professor and has written multiple books and articles on credit and economic stress. She has also been recognized for her work by various publications and professional groups.